Declaration of Banjara / Laman Tanda habitations for implementation of Sewalal Maharaj Banjara / Laman Tanda Samriddhi Yojana.

2 of the Banjara / Laman community nominated by the President of Sadhu Zilla Parishad.
Representative - There is a provision for appointment as a non-official member. But in most of the Zila Parishads, the administrator is working.
Hence, it became necessary to appoint these non-governmental members from the government level. With this in mind
Appointment of non-official members to the committee headed by the Collector, Yavatmal for a period of 3 years.
It was under the consideration of the government.
The Government's Decisions:
Banjara / Laman Tanda to implement Sant Sewalal Maharaj Banjara / Laman Tanda Samriddhi Yojana
Declaring a settlement, declaring a village, taking action to declare Tandaya a revenue village, Gram Panchayat
Under the chairmanship of the District Collector, Yavatmal, the process of formation, etc. and other ancillary proceedings shall be carried out.
2 representatives of Banjara / Laman community as non-official members for 3 years in the district level committee are as follows:
are being appointed.

The non-governmental members concerned shall pay from the fund 2 per cent of the allowable expenditure.
Payments of Daily Allowance and Travel Allowance demanded to Collector, Yavatmal CEO,
